page.title: 01Introduction
page.content:
A lot of our area is made up of pine forests and heathland.
There are a lot of fallow deer in the forests. It is mainly pine but there are a few decidous trees around the outside of the forest.
On the heath there are a lot of adders and grass snakes.There is clay under the heathland and there are lots of ponds which are dug to find clay for a pottery.
There is an{Admiralty Research {Establishment}in our area and many people from Holton Heath are employed there.
We have an {industrial estate}and lots of people work there.
